# Docs on ship / bugfix

Before marking Deck-facing work **done** (feature implementation, plan execution, or bug fix):

1. **`docs/roadmap.md`**
   - **Feature shipped:** remove from **Planned** / **In Progress**; add a line to **`docs/archive/roadmap-completed.md`**; update **Appendix** dependency bullets if needed.
   - **Bug fixed:** remove or resolve the **In Progress → Bugs** row; note fix in completed archive if user-visible.
   - **Partial ship:** move completed scope to **Completed**; leave a smaller **Planned** follow-up.

2. **`docs/testing.md`**
   - Add or update a row in **Shipped feature coverage** (Feature ID, Test ID(s), Status **Open** until on-Deck QA).
   - Add or extend scenario checkboxes / runbook tier when the change needs new QA steps.
   - For bug fixes: note which smoke/scenario now passes or add a regression row.

3. **Same change set** as the code — not a follow-up PR. Docs-only plans (roadmap edits with no code) are exempt.

4. Also update **`docs/troubleshooting.md`** when setup, permissions, or user-facing behavior changes.

Full policy: MCP `bonsai.policy.get` id=`documentation` or [packages/bonsai-mcp/knowledge/policies/documentation.md](../../packages/bonsai-mcp/knowledge/policies/documentation.md).
